{
  "text": "According to [CITATION_1] , because of the plasticity of the canola plant, yields were maintained over a wide range of populations before yields began to decline. Authors suggest that the primary response of canola to lower plant population is increased branching and pods per branch. , the number of pods per plant increases from 20 to 600 and branching per plant increased from 3 to more than 40 branches, thus evidencing the high plasticity capacity of canola.",
